mson Clouds (Short Story Idea, first page)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Dreaming of crimson clouds</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
        Gabriel blinked calmly at the sight, quite contrary to the commotion of the students around him. Fraternity drunks rooted on, making encouraging chants, while the girls all seemed to have mixed emotions about everything, especially whenever the blood spattered onto the cement every so often. A series of thickening thuds sounded in unison with a muffled grunt, and a pattern-esque cracking balanced out the rythmic motions of the violence.<br>
        A young man collapsed to the ground again, and immediately pushed himself up again. A trailed snapping sound, like cracking ice, repeated itself again as the fallen student stumbled to hold his position for an attack. The sound reminded Gabriel of the crunching of chips, and his stomach growled. He’d have to step in soon, if he wanted to get any food later.<br>
        The young man couldn’t have been much older than Gabriel, but his face had been torn and bruised with such sadistic treatment, that his face seemed wrinkled and as if it had aged for fifty years over. He punched forward clumsily, missing both his attackers, and the two opposing students resumed their rythmic brutality. Finally, the victim collapsed to the ground and was without the strength to fight back. His attackers continued to kick their victim, spreading more crimson onto the concrete.<br>
        Stepping into the small ring of the fight, Gabriel was met with a quick shove and a strong punch to his jaw. His lips parted, and he tasted fresh-flowing blood in his mouth. Gabriel blinked, and the crowd pushed and stretched away in a sunburst towards the sky, and only darkness could be seen of them as the light dimmed. The image of the two aggressors warped itself, twisting and expanding and contracting. Gabriel's left arm went numb.<br>
        The darkness swirled, and Gabriel dreamt of black light swirling crimson clouds in ripples of infinite speculars, like sunlight bouncing off steel.<br>
        Ambulance sirens wailed nearby, and Gabriel found himself collapsed across the sidewalk, without the energy to move, a crew of police officers surrounding him. A puzzled expression dominated his face as he was lifted off the ground, and he glanced to the nearby ambulances, and watched the emergency teams lift up the body of a student. Blood spattered over this student’s torn, white, button-down T-shirt, and a stream of blood still oozed freely from his mouth, which had been forced open by a broken jaw. This man’s face was badly beaten, his eyes swollen and sunken, blood bending around the bags of his eyes and the wrinkles of his swollen bruises. The small between his brows was blackened and bevelled, the bone beneath shattered and the skin crushed. The blood trickled down over his left arm and trailed to the cement below him. <br>
        Gabriel glanced to his own arm, realizing a moist sensation on his hand. Deep crimson and black fluids trickled down his knuckles and dripped with every step of movement. <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
